
# About Me
My background is mainly in developing web applications and intranet applications.  I am proficient in HTML and CSS (and have just started using SASS). I program primarily in [Rust](https://www.rust-lang.org/en-US/), JavaScript, PHP.  I have done some programming in C++, C#, Python, VB, and Java.  Haskell is something I have played around with but would not yet consider myself proficient with.

I currently use Windows for everyday use.  Being a web programmer I am no stranger to linux and currently have use [Ubuntu](https://www.ubuntu.com/) as my distro of choice.


# This Website
[Nginx](https://www.nginx.com/)
This website is run on a Ubuntu server using [Nginx](https://www.nginx.com/) as a reverse proxy to serve html files generated by my Rust web app.

[Rocket](https://rocket.rs/)
Nginx servers static files but all other requests go to the Rust application which uses the [Rocket web framework](https://rocket.rs/).  I absolutely love Rocket.  It allows me to write web applications with a focus on traits and types/data structures.

[Let's Encrypt](https://letsencrypt.org/)
Rocket and Nginx both support TLS so using [Let's Encrypt](https://letsencrypt.org/) to encrypt the entire website was an easy decision.  It was easy to setup both Rocket and Nginx to use HTTPS.

[Linode](https://www.linode.com/?r=b0738c61551a05bb0e66386a797c23c1cbf49da6)
When it came time to deploy my Rust web app I needed to choose a VPS to host it.  Previously I have used shared hosting sites like SiteGround but in this case that wouldn't work so my good friend recommended [Linode](https://www.linode.com/?r=b0738c61551a05bb0e66386a797c23c1cbf49da6).  I have found it very easy to use and the prices very fair.  They have a fairly extensive collection of articles to help you setup webservers, use a domain name/subdomain, setup email, and secure your server.  The above links to Linode use my referral code.

