# Miscellaneous
[MusicBee](https://getmusicbee.com/)
Music is a must for many serious programmer.  I have been using [MusicBee](https://getmusicbee.com/) ever since I stopped using Winamp.

[SumatraPDF](https://www.sumatrapdfreader.org/free-pdf-reader.html)
For ebooks I use [SumatraPDF](https://www.sumatrapdfreader.org/free-pdf-reader.html).  It supports pdf's, epub, djvu, mobi, epub, chm, and even comic book and fanfic files.  When I am trying to learn something I find ebooks to be essential, and sumatra makes it easy for me to flip my laptop screen over and read the ebook like I would on a tablet.

[CrypTool](https://www.cryptool.org/de/)
Security is important.  Using encryption tools can be difficult if you are like me and have mostly command line encryption tools.  I use [CrypTool](https://www.cryptool.org/de/) when I need to play around with and convert the data first.  It is also an essential learning tool when trying to understand and learn how cryptography works.

[AutoHotKey](https://autohotkey.com/)
Automating tasks is a must for programmers with limited time.  I have been using [AutoHotKey](https://autohotkey.com/) for many years.  I would highly recommend all Windows programmers learn a little AHK; it's not hard to pick up and can do so many different tasks easily.


